## Why Coaching and Consulting Are Different (And Why It Matters)

Most solopreneurs conflate coaching and consulting. They're not the same.

**Consulting:** You tell them what to do (audit, strategy, recommendations)

**Coaching:** You help them figure it out (accountability, guidance, mindset work)

**Hybrid:** You do both (most common)

The difference matters because it changes:
- Your pricing ($5K vs $50K engagement)
- Your outcome (they execute vs you guide execution)
- Your time (fixed scope vs open-ended)
- Your stress (delivering results vs supporting their process)

Most solopreneurs should start with **hybrid coaching-consulting** because:
1. Easier to position (you're an expert + guide)
2. Higher price point than pure coaching ($10K-$50K packages)
3. Clearer deliverables than pure coaching
4. Less ongoing accountability burden

---

## The Coaching/Consulting Offer Pyramid

High-ticket work follows a pyramid. Pick your level.

### Level 1: Group Coaching ($297-$997/person)

**What it is:** Group calls with pre-recorded content + Slack community

**Your role:** Weekly group call (1 hour), respond to Slack (1-2 hours/week)

**Duration:** 8-12 weeks

**Total revenue:** 20 people × $497 = $9,940

**Your time:** 30 hours total (calls + Slack)

**Hourly rate:** ~$330/hour (solid)

**Best for:** You're building your coaching business. You want recurring revenue. You're comfortable with groups.

**Example:** "12-Week Freelance Business Bootcamp" ($497) for 20 people

### Level 2: 1-on-1 Coaching ($2K-$10K per client)

**What it is:** Bi-weekly calls (45 min each) + email support + accountability

**Your role:** Calls, reviewing work, strategic guidance

**Duration:** 3-6 months

**Total revenue:** 3 clients × $5K = $15,000

**Your time:** 20 hours/month (6 calls + emails + prep)

**Hourly rate:** ~$250/hour (good for coaching)

**Best for:** You have a proven framework. You're selective with clients. You want deeper relationships.

**Example:** "6-Month Brand Building Coaching" ($5,000) with 1-on-1 calls

### Level 3: Consulting Project ($10K-$50K)

**What it is:** Audit + strategy + implementation guidance (no execution by you)

**Your role:** Research, strategy document, 4-6 check-in calls

**Duration:** 6-12 weeks

**Total revenue:** 1 client = $25,000

**Your time:** 40-60 hours total (research heavy)

**Hourly rate:** ~$400-$625/hour

**Best for:** You have deep expertise. You can deliver strategy quickly. You want high-value engagements.

**Example:** "Go-to-Market Strategy Consulting" ($25K) for SaaS founders

### Level 4: Executive Advisory ($50K-$250K+)

**What it is:** Ongoing strategic advisor role + implementation support

**Your role:** Monthly calls + ad hoc advice + accountability

**Duration:** 12 months (retainer)

**Total revenue:** 1 retainer client = $10K-$20K/month

**Your time:** 10-15 hours/month

**Hourly rate:** ~$650-$1,300/hour

**Best for:** You're recognized as a top expert. Clients seek you out. You have a proven track record.

**Example:** "Executive Coach - Growth Strategy" ($15K/month) for CEO

